"Ritratto di S.M. la Regina d' Italia Elena del Montenegro" (1930)

Elena (1873–1952) was born to King Nicholas I of Montenegro and Queen Milena. After her marriage to Victor Emmanuel III of Italy, she serve as Queen of Italy from 1900 until 1946.

At 5 foot 9 inches (180 cm.), Elena was considerably taller than her husband, who was 153 cm. tall. Therefore, she called him "mon petit roi, " meaning "my small king."
